{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So the first question is, why do we need to"},{"time":2000,"text":"even worry about a pandemic threat?"},{"time":5000,"text":"What is it that we're concerned about?"},{"time":7000,"text":"When I say \"we,\" I'm at the Council on Foreign Relations."},{"time":10000,"text":"We're concerned in the national security community,"},{"time":12000,"text":"and of course in the biology community and the public health community."},{"time":15000,"text":"While globalization has increased travel,"},{"time":17000,"text":"it's made it necessary that everybody be everywhere,"},{"time":20000,"text":"all the time, all over the world."},{"time":22000,"text":"And that means that your microbial hitchhikers are moving with you."},{"time":25000,"text":"So a plague outbreak in Surat, India"},{"time":27000,"text":"becomes not an obscure event, but a globalized event --"},{"time":30000,"text":"a globalized concern that has changed the risk equation."},{"time":33000,"text":"Katrina showed us"},{"time":35000,"text":"that we cannot completely depend on government"},{"time":37000,"text":"to have readiness in hand, to be capable of handling things."},{"time":40000,"text":"Indeed, an outbreak would be multiple Katrinas at once."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44000,"text":"Our big concern at the moment is a virus called H5N1 flu --"},{"time":47000,"text":"some of you call it bird flu --"},{"time":49000,"text":"which first emerged in southern China, in the mid-1990s,"},{"time":52000,"text":"but we didn't know about it until 1997."},{"time":55000,"text":"At the end of last Christmas only 13 countries had seen H5N1."},{"time":59000,"text":"But we're now up to 55 countries in the world,"},{"time":61000,"text":"have had this virus emerge,"},{"time":63000,"text":"in either birds, or people or both."},{"time":66000,"text":"In the bird outbreaks we now can see"},{"time":68000,"text":"that pretty much the whole world has seen this virus"},{"time":71000,"text":"except the Americas."},{"time":73000,"text":"And I'll get into why we've so far been spared in a moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77000,"text":"In domestic birds, especially chickens,"},{"time":79000,"text":"it's 100 percent lethal."},{"time":81000,"text":"It's one of the most lethal things we've seen"},{"time":83000,"text":"in circulation in the world"},{"time":85000,"text":"in any recent centuries."},{"time":87000,"text":"And we've dealt with it by killing off lots and lots and lots of chickens,"},{"time":90000,"text":"and unfortunately often not reimbursing the peasant farmers"},{"time":93000,"text":"with the result that there's cover-up."},{"time":95000,"text":"It's also carried on migration patterns"},{"time":97000,"text":"of wild migratory aquatic birds."},{"time":100000,"text":"There has been this centralized event"},{"time":102000,"text":"in a place called Lake Chenghai, China."},{"time":104000,"text":"Two years ago the migrating birds"},{"time":106000,"text":"had a multiple event"},{"time":108000,"text":"where thousands died because of a mutation occurring"},{"time":110000,"text":"in the virus,"},{"time":112000,"text":"which made the species range broaden dramatically."},{"time":115000,"text":"So that birds going to Siberia, to Europe, and to Africa"},{"time":118000,"text":"carried the virus, which had not previously been possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121000,"text":"We're now seeing outbreaks in human populations --"},{"time":125000,"text":"so far, fortunately, small events,"},{"time":128000,"text":"tiny outbreaks, occasional clusters."},{"time":131000,"text":"The virus has mutated dramatically in the last two years"},{"time":134000,"text":"to form two distinct families, if you will,"},{"time":137000,"text":"of the H5N1 viral tree"},{"time":139000,"text":"with branches in them,"},{"time":141000,"text":"and with different attributes that are worrying."},{"time":143000,"text":"So what's concerning us? Well, first of all,"},{"time":145000,"text":"at no time in history have we succeeded in making"},{"time":148000,"text":"in a timely fashion, a specific vaccine"},{"time":150000,"text":"for more than 260 million people."},{"time":153000,"text":"It's not going to do us very much good in a global pandemic."},{"time":156000,"text":"You've heard about the vaccine we're stockpiling."},{"time":159000,"text":"But nobody believes it will actually be particularly effective"},{"time":161000,"text":"if we have a real outbreak."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"So one thought is:"},{"time":165000,"text":"after 9/11, when the airports closed,"},{"time":167000,"text":"our flu season was delayed by two weeks."},{"time":169000,"text":"So the thought is, hey, maybe what we should do is just"},{"time":171000,"text":"immediately -- we hear there is H5N1 spreading from human to human,"},{"time":175000,"text":"the virus has mutated to be a human-to-human transmitter --"},{"time":177000,"text":"let's shut down the airports."},{"time":179000,"text":"However, huge supercomputer analyses,"},{"time":183000,"text":"done of the likely effectiveness of this,"},{"time":185000,"text":"show that it won't buy us much time at all."},{"time":187000,"text":"And of course it will be hugely disruptive in preparation plans."},{"time":191000,"text":"For example, all masks are made in China."},{"time":194000,"text":"How do you get them mobilized around the world"},{"time":196000,"text":"if you've shut all the airports down?"},{"time":198000,"text":"How do you get the vaccines moved around the world"},{"time":200000,"text":"and the drugs moved, and whatever may or not be available that would work."},{"time":203000,"text":"So it turns out that shutting down the airports is counterproductive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"We're worried because this virus, unlike any other flu"},{"time":210000,"text":"we've ever studied, can be transmitted by eating raw meat"},{"time":214000,"text":"of the infected animals."},{"time":216000,"text":"We've seen transmission to wild cats and domestic cats,"},{"time":219000,"text":"and now also domestic pet dogs."},{"time":222000,"text":"And in experimental feedings to rodents and ferrets,"},{"time":225000,"text":"we found that the animals exhibit symptoms never seen with flu:"},{"time":229000,"text":"seizures, central nervous system disorders, partial paralysis."},{"time":232000,"text":"This is not your normal garden-variety flu."},{"time":235000,"text":"It mimics what we now understand"},{"time":237000,"text":"about reconstructing the 1918 flu virus,"},{"time":239000,"text":"the last great pandemic,"},{"time":241000,"text":"in that it also jumped directly from birds to people."},{"time":243000,"text":"We had evolution over time,"},{"time":245000,"text":"and this unbelievable mortality rate in human beings:"},{"time":249000,"text":"55 percent of people who have become infected"},{"time":251000,"text":"with H5N1 have, in fact, succumbed."},{"time":255000,"text":"And we don't have a huge number of people"},{"time":257000,"text":"who got infected and never developed disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260000,"text":"In experimental feeding in monkeys"},{"time":262000,"text":"you can see that it actually downregulates"},{"time":264000,"text":"a specific immune system modulator."},{"time":266000,"text":"The result is that what kills you"},{"time":268000,"text":"is not the virus directly, but your own immune system overreacting, saying,"},{"time":271000,"text":"\"Whatever this is so foreign I'm going berserk.\""},{"time":274000,"text":"The result: most of the deaths"},{"time":276000,"text":"have been in people under 30 years of age,"},{"time":278000,"text":"robustly healthy young adults."},{"time":281000,"text":"We have seen human-to-human transmission"},{"time":283000,"text":"in at least three clusters --"},{"time":285000,"text":"fortunately involving very intimate contact,"},{"time":288000,"text":"still not putting the world at large at any kind of risk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291000,"text":"Alright, so I've got you nervous."},{"time":293000,"text":"Now you probably assume, well the governments are going to do something."},{"time":296000,"text":"And we have spent a lot of money."},{"time":298000,"text":"Most of the spending in the Bush administration"},{"time":300000,"text":"has actually been more related to the anthrax results"},{"time":304000,"text":"and bio-terrorism threat."},{"time":306000,"text":"But a lot of money has been thrown out at the local level and at the federal level"},{"time":309000,"text":"to look at infectious diseases."},{"time":311000,"text":"End result: only 15 states"},{"time":313000,"text":"have been certified to be able to do mass distribution"},{"time":315000,"text":"of vaccine and drugs in a pandemic."},{"time":318000,"text":"Half the states would run out of hospital beds"},{"time":320000,"text":"in the first week, maybe two weeks."},{"time":322000,"text":"And 40 states already have an acute nursing shortage."},{"time":325000,"text":"Add on pandemic threat, you're in big trouble."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327000,"text":"So what have people been doing with this money?"},{"time":329000,"text":"Exercises, drills, all over the world."},{"time":331000,"text":"Let's pretend there's a pandemic."},{"time":333000,"text":"Let's everybody run around and play your role."},{"time":335000,"text":"Main result is that there is tremendous confusion."},{"time":338000,"text":"Most of these people don't actually know what their job will be."},{"time":341000,"text":"And the bottom line, major thing that has come through"},{"time":343000,"text":"in every single drill: nobody knows who's in charge."},{"time":346000,"text":"Nobody knows the chain of command."},{"time":348000,"text":"If it were Los Angeles, is it the mayor, the governor,"},{"time":351000,"text":"the President of the United States, the head of Homeland Security?"},{"time":354000,"text":"In fact, the federal government says it's a guy called"},{"time":356000,"text":"the Principle Federal Officer,"},{"time":359000,"text":"who happens to be with TSA."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361000,"text":"The government says"},{"time":362000,"text":"the federal responsibility will basically be"},{"time":365000,"text":"about trying to keep the virus out, which we all know is impossible,"},{"time":368000,"text":"and then to mitigate the impact"},{"time":370000,"text":"primarily on our economy."},{"time":373000,"text":"The rest is up to your local community."},{"time":375000,"text":"Everything is about your town, where you live."},{"time":378000,"text":"Well how good a city council you have,"},{"time":380000,"text":"how good a mayor you have -- that's who's going to be in charge."},{"time":384000,"text":"Most local facilities would all be competing"},{"time":386000,"text":"to try and get their hands on their piece"},{"time":388000,"text":"of the federal stockpile of a drug called Tamiflu,"},{"time":391000,"text":"which may or may not be helpful -- I'll get into that --"},{"time":393000,"text":"of available vaccines, and any other treatments,"},{"time":396000,"text":"and masks, and anything that's been stockpiled."},{"time":399000,"text":"And you'll have massive competition."},{"time":402000,"text":"Now we did purchase a vaccine, you've probably all heard about it,"},{"time":404000,"text":"made by Sanofi-Aventis."},{"time":406000,"text":"Unfortunately it's made against the current form of H5N1."},{"time":409000,"text":"We know the virus will mutate. It will be a different virus."},{"time":412000,"text":"The vaccine will probably be useless."},{"time":415000,"text":"So here's where the decisions come in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417000,"text":"You're the mayor of your local town."},{"time":419000,"text":"Let's see, should we order that all pets be kept indoors?"},{"time":422000,"text":"Germany did that when H5N1 appeared in Germany last year,"},{"time":425000,"text":"in order to minimize the spread"},{"time":427000,"text":"between households by household cats, dogs and so on."},{"time":431000,"text":"What do we do when we don't have any containment rooms"},{"time":435000,"text":"with reverse air that will allow the healthcare workers"},{"time":437000,"text":"to take care of patients?"},{"time":439000,"text":"These are in Hong Kong; we have nothing like that here."},{"time":441000,"text":"What about quarantine?"},{"time":443000,"text":"During the SARS epidemic in Beijing quarantine did seem to help."},{"time":446000,"text":"We have no uniform policies"},{"time":448000,"text":"regarding quarantine across the United States."},{"time":450000,"text":"And some states have differential policies, county by county."},{"time":454000,"text":"But what about the no-brainer things? Should we close all the schools?"},{"time":457000,"text":"Well then what about all the workers? They won't go to work"},{"time":459000,"text":"if their kids aren't in school."},{"time":461000,"text":"Encouraging telecommuting? What works?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":463000,"text":"Well the British government did a model of telecommuting."},{"time":466000,"text":"Six weeks they had all people in the banking industry"},{"time":469000,"text":"pretend a pandemic was underway."},{"time":471000,"text":"What they found was, the core functions --"},{"time":473000,"text":"you know you still sort of had banks,"},{"time":475000,"text":"but you couldn't get people to put money in the ATM machines."},{"time":478000,"text":"Nobody was processing the credit cards."},{"time":480000,"text":"Your insurance payments didn't go through."},{"time":482000,"text":"And basically the economy would be in a disaster state of affairs."},{"time":485000,"text":"And that's just office workers, bankers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489000,"text":"We don't know how important hand washing is for flu --"},{"time":492000,"text":"shocking. One assumes it's a good idea to wash your hands a lot."},{"time":495000,"text":"But actually in scientific community there is great debate"},{"time":497000,"text":"about what percentage of flu transmission between people"},{"time":500000,"text":"is from sneezing and coughing"},{"time":502000,"text":"and what percentage is on your hands."},{"time":504000,"text":"The Institute of Medicine tried to look at the masking question."},{"time":508000,"text":"Can we figure out a way, since we know we won't have enough masks"},{"time":510000,"text":"because we don't make them in America anymore,"},{"time":512000,"text":"they're all made in China --"},{"time":514000,"text":"do we need N95? A state-of-the-art, top-of-the-line,"},{"time":517000,"text":"must-be-fitted-to-your-face mask?"},{"time":520000,"text":"Or can we get away with some different kinds of masks?"},{"time":523000,"text":"In the SARS epidemic, we learned in Hong Kong"},{"time":525000,"text":"that most of transmission was because"},{"time":527000,"text":"people were removing their masks improperly."},{"time":529000,"text":"And their hand got contaminated with the outside of the mask,"},{"time":531000,"text":"and then they rubbed their nose. Bingo! They got SARS."},{"time":534000,"text":"It wasn't flying microbes."},{"time":537000,"text":"If you go online right now, you'll get so much phony-baloney information."},{"time":540000,"text":"You'll end up buying -- this is called an N95 mask. Ridiculous."},{"time":545000,"text":"We don't actually have a standard"},{"time":547000,"text":"for what should be the protective gear for the first responders,"},{"time":550000,"text":"the people who will actually be there on the front lines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553000,"text":"And Tamiflu. You've probably heard of this drug,"},{"time":555000,"text":"made by Hoffmann-La Roche, patented drug."},{"time":558000,"text":"There is some indication"},{"time":560000,"text":"that it may buy you some time in the midst of an outbreak."},{"time":563000,"text":"Should you take Tamiflu for a long period of time,"},{"time":565000,"text":"well, one of the side effects is suicidal ideations."},{"time":568000,"text":"A public health survey analyzed the effect"},{"time":572000,"text":"that large-scale Tamiflu use would have,"},{"time":574000,"text":"actually shows it counteractive"},{"time":576000,"text":"to public health measures, making matters worse."},{"time":579000,"text":"And here is the other interesting thing:"},{"time":581000,"text":"when a human being ingests Tamiflu, only 20 percent"},{"time":583000,"text":"is metabolized appropriately"},{"time":585000,"text":"to be an active compound in the human being."},{"time":587000,"text":"The rest turns into a stable compound,"},{"time":591000,"text":"which survives filtration into the water systems,"},{"time":594000,"text":"thereby exposing the very aquatic birds that would carry flu"},{"time":597000,"text":"and providing them a chance"},{"time":599000,"text":"to breed resistant strains."},{"time":601000,"text":"And we now have seen Tamiflu-resistant strains"},{"time":604000,"text":"in both Vietnam in person-to-person transmission,"},{"time":607000,"text":"and in Egypt in person-to-person transmission."},{"time":609000,"text":"So I personally think that our life expectancy"},{"time":612000,"text":"for Tamiflu as an effective drug"},{"time":615000,"text":"is very limited -- very limited indeed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617000,"text":"Nevertheless most of the governments"},{"time":619000,"text":"have based their whole flu policies"},{"time":621000,"text":"on building stockpiles of Tamiflu."},{"time":623000,"text":"Russia has actually stockpiled enough"},{"time":625000,"text":"for 95 percent of all Russians."},{"time":627000,"text":"We've stockpiled enough for 30 percent."},{"time":629000,"text":"When I say enough, that's two weeks worth."},{"time":631000,"text":"And then you're on your own because"},{"time":633000,"text":"the pandemic is going to last for 18 to 24 months."},{"time":635000,"text":"Some of the poorer countries"},{"time":637000,"text":"that have had the most experience with H5N1 have built up stockpiles;"},{"time":640000,"text":"they're already expired. They are already out of date."},{"time":643000,"text":"What do we know from 1918,"},{"time":645000,"text":"the last great pandemic?"},{"time":647000,"text":"The federal government abdicated most responsibility."},{"time":650000,"text":"And so we ended up with this wild patchwork of regulations"},{"time":653000,"text":"all over America."},{"time":655000,"text":"Every city, county, state did their own thing."},{"time":657000,"text":"And the rules"},{"time":659000,"text":"and the belief systems were wildly disparate."},{"time":662000,"text":"In some cases all schools, all churches,"},{"time":665000,"text":"all public venues were closed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667000,"text":"The pandemic circulated three times in 18 months"},{"time":670000,"text":"in the absence of commercial air travel."},{"time":672000,"text":"The second wave was the mutated, super-killer wave."},{"time":675000,"text":"And in the first wave we had enough healthcare workers."},{"time":678000,"text":"But by the time the second wave hit"},{"time":680000,"text":"it took such a toll among the healthcare workers"},{"time":683000,"text":"that we lost most of our doctors and nurses that were on the front lines."},{"time":687000,"text":"Overall we lost 700,000 people."},{"time":689000,"text":"The virus was 100 percent lethal to pregnant women"},{"time":692000,"text":"and we don't actually know why."},{"time":694000,"text":"Most of the death toll was 15 to 40 year-olds --"},{"time":697000,"text":"robustly healthy young adults."},{"time":699000,"text":"It was likened to the plague."},{"time":701000,"text":"We don't actually know how many people died."},{"time":703000,"text":"The low-ball estimate is 35 million."},{"time":706000,"text":"This was based on European and North American data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709000,"text":"A new study by Chris Murray at Harvard"},{"time":711000,"text":"shows that if you look at the databases that were kept"},{"time":713000,"text":"by the Brits in India,"},{"time":715000,"text":"there was a 31-fold greater death rate among the Indians."},{"time":719000,"text":"So there is a strong belief that in places of poverty"},{"time":722000,"text":"the death toll was far higher."},{"time":724000,"text":"And that a more likely toll"},{"time":726000,"text":"is somewhere in the neighborhood of 80 to 100 million people"},{"time":728000,"text":"before we had commercial air travel."},{"time":731000,"text":"So are we ready?"},{"time":733000,"text":"As a nation, no we're not."},{"time":735000,"text":"And I think even those in the leadership"},{"time":737000,"text":"would say that is the case,"},{"time":739000,"text":"that we still have a long ways to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741000,"text":"So what does that mean for you? Well the first thing is,"},{"time":743000,"text":"I wouldn't start building up personal stockpiles of anything --"},{"time":746000,"text":"for yourself, your family, or your employees --"},{"time":750000,"text":"unless you've really done your homework."},{"time":753000,"text":"What mask works, what mask doesn't work."},{"time":755000,"text":"How many masks do you need?"},{"time":757000,"text":"The Institute of Medicine study felt that"},{"time":759000,"text":"you could not recycle masks."},{"time":761000,"text":"Well if you think it's going to last 18 months,"},{"time":764000,"text":"are you going to buy 18 months worth of masks"},{"time":766000,"text":"for every single person in your family?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"We don't know -- again with Tamiflu,"},{"time":773000,"text":"the number one side effect of Tamiflu is"},{"time":775000,"text":"flu-like symptoms."},{"time":777000,"text":"So then how can you tell"},{"time":779000,"text":"who in your family has the flu"},{"time":781000,"text":"if everybody is taking Tamiflu?"},{"time":784000,"text":"If you expand that out to think of a whole community,"},{"time":787000,"text":"or all your employees in your company,"},{"time":790000,"text":"you begin to realize how limited"},{"time":792000,"text":"the Tamiflu option might be."},{"time":794000,"text":"Everybody has come up to me and said,"},{"time":796000,"text":"well I'll stockpile water or, I'll stockpile food, or what have you."},{"time":800000,"text":"But really? Do you really have a place"},{"time":803000,"text":"to stockpile 18 months worth of food? Twenty-four months worth of food?"},{"time":806000,"text":"Do you want to view the pandemic threat"},{"time":808000,"text":"the way back in the 1950s"},{"time":810000,"text":"people viewed the civil defense issue,"},{"time":812000,"text":"and build your own little bomb shelter for pandemic flu?"},{"time":815000,"text":"I don't think that's rational."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817000,"text":"I think it's about having to be prepared"},{"time":819000,"text":"as communities, not as individuals --"},{"time":821000,"text":"being prepared as nation,"},{"time":823000,"text":"being prepared as state, being prepared as town."},{"time":826000,"text":"And right now most of the preparedness"},{"time":828000,"text":"is deeply flawed."},{"time":830000,"text":"And I hope I've convinced you of that,"},{"time":832000,"text":"which means that the real job is go out and"},{"time":834000,"text":"say to your local leaders,"},{"time":836000,"text":"and your national leaders,"},{"time":838000,"text":"\"Why haven't you solved these problems?"},{"time":840000,"text":"Why are you still thinking that"},{"time":842000,"text":"the lessons of Katrina do not apply to flu?\""},{"time":845000,"text":"And put the pressure where the pressure needs to be put."},{"time":849000,"text":"But I guess the other thing to add is,"},{"time":851000,"text":"if you do have employees, and you do have a company,"},{"time":853000,"text":"I think you have certain responsibilities"},{"time":856000,"text":"to demonstrate that you are thinking ahead for them,"},{"time":858000,"text":"and you are trying to plan."},{"time":860000,"text":"At a minimum the British banking plan showed that"},{"time":864000,"text":"telecommuting can be helpful."},{"time":866000,"text":"It probably does reduce exposure"},{"time":868000,"text":"because people are not coming into the office and coughing on each other,"},{"time":871000,"text":"or touching common objects"},{"time":874000,"text":"and sharing things via their hands."},{"time":876000,"text":"But can you sustain your company that way?"},{"time":880000,"text":"Well if you have a dot-com, maybe you can."},{"time":883000,"text":"Otherwise you're in trouble."},{"time":886000,"text":"Happy to take your questions."},{"time":888000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":892000,"text":"Audience member: What factors determine the duration of a pandemic?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":897000,"text":"Laurie Garret: What factors determine the duration of a pandemic, we don't really know."},{"time":901000,"text":"I could give you a bunch of flip, this, that, and the other."},{"time":904000,"text":"But I would say that honestly we don't know."},{"time":907000,"text":"Clearly the bottom line is"},{"time":909000,"text":"the virus eventually attenuates,"},{"time":912000,"text":"and ceases to be a lethal virus to humanity,"},{"time":917000,"text":"and finds other hosts."},{"time":919000,"text":"But we don't really know how and why that happens."},{"time":921000,"text":"It's a very complicated ecology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":924000,"text":"Audience member: What kind of triggers are you looking for?"},{"time":927000,"text":"You know way more than any of us."},{"time":929000,"text":"To say ahh, if this happens then we are going to have a pandemic?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":933000,"text":"LG: The moment that you see any evidence"},{"time":935000,"text":"of serious human-to-human to transmission."},{"time":938000,"text":"Not just intimately between family members"},{"time":940000,"text":"who took care of an ailing sister or brother,"},{"time":944000,"text":"but a community infected --"},{"time":946000,"text":"spread within a school,"},{"time":948000,"text":"spread within a dormitory, something of that nature."},{"time":951000,"text":"Then I think that there is universal agreement"},{"time":954000,"text":"now, at WHO all the way down:"},{"time":956000,"text":"Send out the alert."}]},{"cues":[{"time":960000,"text":"Audience member: Some research has indicated that statins can be helpful."},{"time":964000,"text":"Can you talk about that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":966000,"text":"LG: Yeah. There is some evidence that taking Lipitor"},{"time":968000,"text":"and other common statins for cholesterol control"},{"time":971000,"text":"may decrease your vulnerability"},{"time":975000,"text":"to influenza."},{"time":977000,"text":"But we do not completely understand why."},{"time":980000,"text":"The mechanism isn't clear."},{"time":982000,"text":"And I don't know that there is any way"},{"time":987000,"text":"responsibly for someone to start"},{"time":990000,"text":"medicating their children"},{"time":992000,"text":"with their personal supply of Lipitor or something of that nature."},{"time":996000,"text":"We have absolutely no idea what that would do."},{"time":998000,"text":"You might be causing some very dangerous outcomes"},{"time":1001000,"text":"in your children, doing such a thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1004000,"text":"Audience member: How far along are we in being able to determine"},{"time":1006000,"text":"whether someone is actually carrying, whether somebody has this"},{"time":1008000,"text":"before the symptoms are full-blown?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1010000,"text":"LG: Right. So I have for a long time said"},{"time":1013000,"text":"that what we really needed was a rapid diagnostic."},{"time":1016000,"text":"And our Centers for Disease Control"},{"time":1019000,"text":"has labeled a test they developed"},{"time":1022000,"text":"a rapid diagnostic."},{"time":1024000,"text":"It takes 24 hours in a very highly developed laboratory,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"in highly skilled hands."},{"time":1030000,"text":"I'm thinking dipstick."},{"time":1032000,"text":"You could do it to your own kid. It changes color."},{"time":1034000,"text":"It tells you if you have H5N1."},{"time":1036000,"text":"In terms of where we are in science"},{"time":1040000,"text":"with DNA identification capacities and so on,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"it's not that far off."},{"time":1046000,"text":"But we're not there. And there hasn't been the kind of investment to get us there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1051000,"text":"Audience member: In the 1918 flu I understand that"},{"time":1054000,"text":"they theorized that there was some attenuation"},{"time":1058000,"text":"of the virus when it made the leap into humans."},{"time":1060000,"text":"Is that likely, do you think, here?"},{"time":1062000,"text":"I mean 100 percent death rate"},{"time":1066000,"text":"is pretty severe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1068000,"text":"LG: Um yeah. So we don't actually know"},{"time":1072000,"text":"what the lethality was"},{"time":1075000,"text":"of the 1918 strain to wild birds"},{"time":1079000,"text":"before it jumped from birds to humans."},{"time":1081000,"text":"It's curious that there is no evidence"},{"time":1083000,"text":"of mass die-offs of chickens"},{"time":1085000,"text":"or household birds across America"},{"time":1088000,"text":"before the human pandemic happened."},{"time":1090000,"text":"That may be because those events"},{"time":1092000,"text":"were occurring on the other side of the world"},{"time":1094000,"text":"where nobody was paying attention."},{"time":1096000,"text":"But the virus clearly"},{"time":1100000,"text":"went through one round around the world"},{"time":1102000,"text":"in a mild enough form"},{"time":1104000,"text":"that the British army in World War I"},{"time":1107000,"text":"actually certified that it was not a threat"},{"time":1110000,"text":"and would not affect the outcome of the war."},{"time":1113000,"text":"And after circulating around the world"},{"time":1115000,"text":"came back in a form that was tremendously lethal."},{"time":1120000,"text":"What percentage of infected people were killed by it?"},{"time":1123000,"text":"Again we don't really know for sure."},{"time":1126000,"text":"It's clear that if you were malnourished to begin with,"},{"time":1128000,"text":"you had a weakened immune system,"},{"time":1130000,"text":"you lived in poverty in India or Africa,"},{"time":1133000,"text":"your likelihood of dying was far greater."},{"time":1136000,"text":"But we don't really know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1139000,"text":"Audience member: One of the things I've heard is that"},{"time":1141000,"text":"the real death cause when you get a flu is the associated pneumonia,"},{"time":1144000,"text":"and that a pneumonia vaccine"},{"time":1146000,"text":"may offer you 50 percent better chance of survival."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1150000,"text":"LG: For a long time, researchers in emerging diseases"},{"time":1154000,"text":"were kind of dismissive of the pandemic flu threat"},{"time":1156000,"text":"on the grounds that"},{"time":1158000,"text":"back in 1918 they didn't have antibiotics."},{"time":1160000,"text":"And that most people who die of regular flu --"},{"time":1163000,"text":"which in regular flu years"},{"time":1165000,"text":"is about 360,000 people worldwide,"},{"time":1168000,"text":"most of them senior citizens --"},{"time":1170000,"text":"and they die not of the flu but because the flu gives an assault to their immune system."},{"time":1174000,"text":"And along comes pneumococcus"},{"time":1176000,"text":"or another bacteria, streptococcus"},{"time":1178000,"text":"and boom, they get a bacterial pneumonia."},{"time":1180000,"text":"But it turns out that in 1918 that was not the case at all."},{"time":1183000,"text":"And so far in the H5N1 cases in people,"},{"time":1186000,"text":"similarly bacterial infection"},{"time":1188000,"text":"has not been an issue at all."},{"time":1190000,"text":"It's this absolutely phenomenal disruption of the immune system"},{"time":1195000,"text":"that is the key to why people die of this virus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1198000,"text":"And I would just add"},{"time":1200000,"text":"we saw the same thing with SARS."},{"time":1202000,"text":"So what's going on here is your body says,"},{"time":1205000,"text":"your immune system sends out all its sentinels and says,"},{"time":1209000,"text":"\"I don't know what the heck this is."},{"time":1211000,"text":"We've never seen anything even remotely like this before.\""},{"time":1214000,"text":"It won't do any good to bring in the sharpshooters"},{"time":1217000,"text":"because those antibodies aren't here."},{"time":1219000,"text":"And it won't do any good to bring in the tanks and the artillery"},{"time":1222000,"text":"because those T-cells don't recognize it either."},{"time":1225000,"text":"So we're going to have to go all-out thermonuclear response,"},{"time":1228000,"text":"stimulate the total cytokine cascade."},{"time":1231000,"text":"The whole immune system swarms into the lungs."},{"time":1234000,"text":"And yes they die, drowning in their own fluids, of pneumonia."},{"time":1237000,"text":"But it's not bacterial pneumonia."},{"time":1239000,"text":"And it's not a pneumonia that would respond to a vaccine."},{"time":1243000,"text":"And I think my time is up. I thank you all for your attention."},{"time":1246000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}